obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (15677)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15677&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Government of Union`
  line `Territories Act, 1963.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that it shall come into force in the Union territory of Mizoram on such date, being a date not`
  line `earlier than the date of commencement of the Government of Union Territories (Amendment) Act, 1971`
  line `(83 of 1971), as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint:]`
  line
  line `^3[Provided further that it shall come into force in the Union territory of Arunachal Pradesh on such`
  line `date, being a date not earlier than the date of commencement of the Government of Union Territories`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 1975 (29 of 1975), as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, appoint:]`
  line
  line `^4[Provided also that, subject to the preceding provisos,] different dates may be appointed for different`
  line `provisions of this Act and for different Union territories and any reference in any such provision to the`
  line `commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to the coming into force of that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 13-5-1963, vide notificationNo. G.S.R. 814, dated 13-5-1963, in respect of Part I, sections 3, 4 and 14 of Part II, Part III,`
  line `sections 53, 56 and 57 of Part V and First and Second Schedulesas applicable to the Union territory of Goa, Daman and Diu,`
  line `see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, Section 3(i).`
  line
  line `20-12-1963, vide notification. No. G.S.R 1922, dated 16-12-1963, in respect of remaining provisions of the Act applicable to`
  line `the Union territory of Goa, Daman and Diu, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, Section 3(i).`
  line
  line `17-2-1972, vide notification No. G.S.R. 81(E), dated 16-2-1972, in respect of sections 1, 2, 3, 4, 14, 38, 43A and 56 of the Act`
  line `shall come into force in the Union territory of Mizoram, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, Section 3(i).`
  line
  line `3-5-1972, vide notification No. G.S.R. 269(E), dated 30-4-1972, in respect of all the provisions of the Act, other than those`
  line `which have already come into force in the Union territory of Mizoram, shall, so far as they are applicable, come into force in`
  line `that Union territory, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, Section 3(i).`
  line
  line `13-5-1963, vide notification. No. G.S.R. 815, dated 13-5-1963, in respect of Part I, sections 53, 56 and 57 of Part V and the`
  line `Second Schedule in the Union territory of Pondicherry, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, Section 3(i).`
  line
  line `1-7-1963, vide notification No. G.S.R. 1025, dated 15-6-1963,for the remaining provisions came into force in theUnion`
  line `territory of Pondicherry, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, Section 3(i).`
  line
  line `1-7-1963, vide notification No. S.O. 1660, dated 14-6-1963,in respect of all the provisions in the Union territories of Himachal`
  line `Pradesh, Manipur and Tripura, and so much of the provisions as apply to the Union territory of Delhi, see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, Section 3(ii).`
  line
  line `1-7-1963, vide notification No. G.S.R. 1025, dated 15-6-1963,in respect of the provisions as apply to the Union territory of`
  line `Dadra and Nagar Haveli, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, Section 3(i).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 83 of 1971, s. 2 (w.e.f. 16-2-1972).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 29 of 1975, s. 2 (w.e.f. 15-8-1975).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "Provided further that" (w.e.f. 15-8-1975).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (15678)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Definitions and interpretation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15678&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,―`
  line
  line `(a) "Administrator" means the administrator of ^1[the Union territory] appointed by the President`
  line `under artcle 239;`
  line
  line `(b) "article" means an article of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(c) "assembly constituency" means a constituency provided under this Act for the purpose of`
  line `elections to the Legislative Assembly of ^1[the Union territory];`
  line
  line `(d) "Election Commission" means the Election Commission appointed by the President under`
  line `article 324;`
  line
  line `(e) "Judicial Commissioner" includes an Additional Judicial Commissioner;`
  line
  line `(f) "scheduled castes" in relation to ^1[the Union territory] means such castes, races or tribes or`
  line `parts of or groups within such castes, races or tribes as are deemed under article 341 to be scheduled`
  line `castes in relation to that Union territory;`
  line
  line `(g) "scheduled tribes" in relation to ^1[the Union territory] means such tribes or tribal communities`
  line `or parts of or groups within such tribes or tribal communities as are deemed under article 342 to be`
  line `scheduled tribes in relation to that Union territory;`
  line
  line `^2[(h) "Union territory" means the Union territory of ^3[Puducherry].`
  line
  line `(2) Any reference in this Act to laws made by Parliament shall be construed as including a reference`
  line `to Ordinances promulgated by the President under article 123 and a reference to Regulations made by the`
  line `President under article 240.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 65, ibid., for clause (h) (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 44 of 2006, s. 7, for "Pondicherry" (w.e.f. 1-10-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (15679)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Legislative Assemblies for Union territories and their composition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15679&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a`
  line `Legislative Assembly for each Union territory.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) The total number of seats in the Legislative Assembly of ^2[the Union territory] to be filled by`
  line `persons chosen by direct election shall be thirty.]`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may nominate not more than three persons, not being persons in the`
  line `service of Government, to be members of the Legislative Assembly of ^2[the Union territory].`
  line
  line `^3[(4) Seats shall be reserved for the Scheduled Castes in the Legislative Assembly of the Union`
  line territory.]
  line
  line `(5) The number of seats reserved for the scheduled castes or the scheduled tribes in the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of ^2[the Union territory] under sub-section (4) shall bear, as nearly as may be, the same`
  line `proportion to the total number of seats in the Assembly as the population of the scheduled castes in the`
  line `Union territory or of the scheduled tribes in the Union territory, as the case may be, in respect of which`
  line `seats are so reserved, bears to the total population of the Union territory.`
  line
  line `^4[Explanation.―In this sub-section, the expression "population" means the population as ascertained`
  line `at the last preceding census of which the relevant figures have been published:`
  line
  line `Provided that the reference in this Explanation to the last preceding census of which the relevant`
  line `figures have been published shall, until the relevant figures for the first census taken after the year ^5[2026] ^5[2026] have been published, be construed as a reference to the ^6[2001] census.]`
  line
  line `^7[(6) Notwithstanding anything in sub-section (4), the reservation of seats for the Scheduled Castes in`
  line `in the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory shall cease to have effect on the same date on which`
  line `the reservation of seats for the Scheduled Castes in the House of the People shall cease to have effect`
  line `under article 334:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall affect any representation in the Legislative Assembly`
  line `of the Union territory until the dissolution of the then existing Assembly.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the State of Himachal Pradesh (Adaptation of Laws on Union Subjects) Order, 1973, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 25-1-1971).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 65, ibid.,for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
  line
  line `4. The Explanation ins. by Act 19 of 1984, s. 2 (w.e.f. 8-5-1984).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 19 of 2005, s. 2, for "2000" (w.e.f. 21-5-2005).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "1971" (w.e.f. 21-5-2005).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for sub-section (6) (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (15680)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Qualification for membership of Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15680&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `A person shall not be qualified to be`
  line `chosen to fill a seat in the Legislative Assembly of ^1[the Union territory] unless he—`
  line
  line `(a) is a citizen of India and makes and subscribes before some person authorised in that behalf by`
  line `the Election Commission an oath or affirmation according to the form set out for the purpose in the`
  line `First Schedule;`
  line
  line `(b) is not less than twenty-five years of age; and`
  line
  line `(c) possesses such other qualifications as may be prescribed in that behalf by or under any law.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (15681)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Duration of Legislative Assemblies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15681&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The Legislative Assembly of ^1[the Union territory], unless`
  line `sooner dissolved, shall continue for five years from the date appointed for its first meeting and no longer,`
  line `and the expiration of the said period of five years shall operate as a dissolution of the Assembly:`
  line
  line `Provided that the said period may, while a Proclamation of Emergency issued under clause (1) of`
  line `article 352 is in operation, be extended by the President by order for a period not exceeding one year at a`
  line `time and not extending in any case beyond a period of six months after the Proclamation has ceased to`
  line operate.
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (15682)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Sessions of Legislative Assembly, prorogation and dissolution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15682&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Administrator shall,`
  line `from time to time, summon the Legislative Assembly to meet at such time and place as he thinks fit, but`
  line `six months shall not intervene between its last sitting in one session and the date appointed for its first`
  line `sitting in the next session.`
  line
  line `(2) The Administrator may, from time to time,―`
  line
  line `(a) prorogue the Assembly;`
  line
  line `(b) dissolve the Assembly`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (15683)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Speaker and Deputy Speaker of Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15683&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Legislative Assembly shall,`
  line `as soon as may be, choose two members of the Assembly to be respectively Speaker and Deputy Speaker`
  line `thereof and, so often as the office of Speaker or Deputy Speaker becomes vacant, the Assembly shall`
  line `choose another member to be Speaker or Deputy Speaker, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) A member holding office as Speaker or Deputy Speaker of an Assembly—`
  line
  line `(a) shall vacate his office if he ceases to be a member of the Assembly;`
  line
  line `(b) may at any time by writing under his hand addressed, if such member is the Speaker, to the`
  line `Deputy Speaker, and if such member is the Deputy Speaker, to the Speaker, resign his office;`
  line
  line `(c) may be removed from his office by a resolution of the Assembly passed by a majority of all`
  line `the then members of the Assembly:`
  line
  line `Provided that no resolution for the purpose of clause (c) shall be moved unless at least fourteen days'`
  line `notice has been given of the intention to move the resolution:`
  line
  line `Provided further that whenever the Assembly is dissolved, the Speaker shall not vacate his office until`
  line `immediately before the first meeting of the Assembly after the dissolution.`
  line
  line `(3) While the office of Speaker is vacant, the duties of the office shall be performed by the Deputy`
  line `Speaker or, if the office of Deputy Speaker is also vacant, by such member of the Assembly as may be`
  line `determined by the rules of procedure of the Assembly.`
  line
  line `(4) During the absence of the Speaker from any sitting of the Assembly, the Deputy Speaker, or, if he`
  line `is also absent, such person as may be determined by the rules of procedure of the Assembly, or, if no such`
  line `person is present, such other person as may be determined by the Assembly, shall act as Speaker.`
  line
  line `(5) There shall be paid to the Speaker and the Deputy Speaker of the Legislative Assembly such`
  line `salaries and allowances as may be respectively fixed by the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory`
  line `by law and, until provision in that behalf is so made, such salaries and allowances as the Administrator`
  line `may, with the approval of the President, by order determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (15684)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Speaker or Deputy Speaker not to preside while a resolution for his removal from office is under consideration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15684&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) At any sitting of the Legislative Assembly, while any resolution for the`
  line `removal of the Speaker from his office is under consideration, the Speaker, or while any resolution for the`
  line `removal of the Deputy Speaker from his office is under consideration, the Deputy Speaker, shall not,`
  line `though he is present, preside and the provisions of sub-section (4) of section 7 shall apply in relation to`
  line `every such sitting as they apply in relation to a sitting from which the Speaker or, as the case may be, the`
  line `Deputy Speaker is absent.`
  line
  line `(2) The Speaker shall have the right to speak in, and otherwise to take part in the proceedings of, the`
  line `Legislative Assembly while any resolution for his removal from office is under consideration in the`
  line `Assembly and shall, notwithstanding anything in section 12, be entitled to vote only in the first instance`
  line `on such resolution or on any other matter during such proceedings but not in the case of an equality of`
  line votes.
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (15685)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Right of Administrator to address and send messages to Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15685&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Administrator may address the Legislative Assembly and may for that purpose require the attendance of`
  line members.
  line
  line `(2) The Administrator may also send messages to the Assembly whether with respect to a Bill then`
  line `pending in the Assembly or otherwise, and when a message is so sent, the Assembly shall with all`
  line `convenient dispatch consider any matter required by the message to be taken into consideration.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (15686)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Rights of Ministers as respects Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15686&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Every Minister shall have the right to`
  line `speak in, and otherwise to take part in the proceedings of, the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory,`
  line `and to speak in, and otherwise to take part in the proceedings of, any committee of the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of which he may be named a member, but shall not by virtue of this section be entitled to vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (15687)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Oath or affirmation by members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65 for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15687&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Every member of the Legislative Assembly of ^1[the Union`
  line `territory] shall, before taking his seat, make and subscribe before the Administrator, or some person`
  line `appointed in that behalf by him, an oath or affirmation according to the form set out for the purpose in the`
  line `First Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (15688)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Voting in Assembly, power of Assembly to act notwithstanding vacancies and quorum.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65 for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15688&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act, all questions at any sitting of the Legislative Assembly of ^1[the`
  line `Union territory] shallbe determined by a majority of votes of the members present and voting other than`
  line `the Speaker or person acting as such.`
  line
  line `(2) The Speaker or person acting as such shall not vote in the first instance but shall have and exercise`
  line `a casting vote in the case of an equality of votes.`
  line
  line `(3) The Legislative Assembly of ^1[the Union territory] shall have power to act notwithstanding any`
  line `vacancy in the membership thereof, and any proceedings in the Legislative Assembly of ^1[the Union`
  line `territory] shall be valid notwithstanding that it is discovered subsequently that some person who was not`
  line `entitled so to do, sat or voted or otherwise took part in the proceedings.`
  line
  line `(4) The quorum to constitute a meeting of the Legislative Assembly of ^1[the Union territory] shall be`
  line `one-third of the total number of members of the Assembly.`
  line
  line `(5) If at any time during a meeting of the Legislative Assembly of ^1[the Union territory] there is no`
  line `quorum, it shall be the duty of the Speaker, or person acting as such, either to adjourn the Assembly or to`
  line `suspend the meeting until there is a quorum.`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (15689)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Vacation of seats.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15689&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall be a member both of Parliament and of the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of ^1[the Union territory] and if a person is chosen a member both of Parliament and of such`
  line `Assembly, then, at the expiration of such period as may be specified in the rules made by the President,`
  line `that person's seat in Parliament shall become vacant, unless he has previously resigned his seat in the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of the Union territory.`
  line
  line `(2) If a member of the Legislative Assembly of ^1[the Union territory]—`
  line
  line `(a) becomes subject to any disqualification mentioned in ^2[section 14 or section 14A] for`
  line `membership of the Assembly, or`
  line
  line `(b) resigns his seat by writing under his hand addressed to the Speaker,`
  line
  line `his seat shall thereupon become vacant.`
  line
  line `(3) If for a period of sixty days a member of the Legislative Assembly of ^1[the union territory] is`
  line `without permission of the Assembly absent from all meetings thereof, the Assembly may declare his seat`
  line `vacant:`
  line
  line `Provided that in computing the said period of sixty days, no account shall be taken of any period`
  line `during which the Assembly is prorogued or is adjourned for more than four consecutive days.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 24 of 1985, s. 2, for "section 14" (w.e.f. 29-3-1985).`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (15690)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Disqualifications for membership.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15690&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall be disqualified for being chosen as, and`
  line `for being, a member of the Legislative Assembly of ^1[the Union territory]--`
  line
  line `(a) if he holds any office of profit under the Government of India or the Government of any State`
  line `or the Government of ^2[the Union territory] other than an office declared by law made by Parliament`
  line `or by the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory not to disqualify its holder; or`
  line
  line `(b) if he is for the time being disqualified for being chosen as, and for being, a member of either`
  line `House of Parliament under the provisions of sub-clause (b), sub-clause (c) or sub-clause (d) of clause`
  line `(1) of article 102 or of any law made in pursuance of that article.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section, a person shall not be deemed to hold an office of profit under the`
  line `Government of India or the Government of any State or the Government of ^2[the Union territory] by`
  line `reason only that he is a Minister either for the Union or for such State or Union territory.`
  line
  line `(3) If any question arises as to whether a member of the Legislative Assembly of ^1[the Union`
  line `territory] has become disqualified for being such a member under the provisions of sub-section (1), the`
  line `question shall be referred for the decision of the President and his decision shall be final.`
  line
  line `(4) Before giving any decision on any such question, the President shall obtain the opinion of the`
  line `Election Commission and shall act according to such opinion.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "any Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_14_a:
  sectionId (15691)
  sectionNo 14A
  orderNo 15
  title `Disqualification on ground of defection for being a member.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15691&sectionno=14A&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_14_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[14A. Disqualification on ground of defection for being a member.--The provisions of the Tenth`
  line `Schedule to the Constitution shall, subject to the necessary modifications (including modifications for`
  line `construing references therein to the Legislative Assembly of a State, article 188, article 194 and article`
  line `212 as references, respectively, to the Legislative Assembly of ^2[the Union territory], section 11, section`
  line `16 and section 37 of this Act), apply to and in relation to the members of the Legislative Assembly of`
  line `^2[the Union territory] as they apply to and in relation to the members of the Legislative Assembly of a`
  line `State, and accordingly,--`
  line
  line `(a) the said Tenth Schedule as so modified shall be deemed to form part of this Act; and`
  line
  line `(b) a person shall be disqualified for being a member of the Legislative Assembly of ^2[the Union`
  line `territory] if he is so disqualified under the said Tenth Schedule as so modified.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 24 of 1985, s. 3 (w.e.f. 29-3-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (15692)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 16
  title `Penalty for sitting and voting before making oath or affirmation or when not qualified or when disqualified.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15692&sectionno=15&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `If a person sits or votes as a member of the Legislative Assembly of ^1[the Union`
  line `territory] before he has complied with the requirements of section 11 or when he knows that he is not`
  line `qualified or that he is disqualified for membership thereof, he shall be liable in respect of each day on`
  line `which he so sits or votes to a penalty of five hundred rupees to be recovered as a debt due to the Union.`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (15693)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 17
  title `Powers, privileges, etc., of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15693&sectionno=16&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act and to the rules`
  line `and standing orders regulating the procedure of the Legislative Assembly, there shall be freedom of`
  line `speech in the Legislative Assembly of ^1[the Union territory].`
  line
  line `(2) No member of the Legislative Assembly of ^2[the Union territory] shall be liable to any`
  line `proceedings in any court in respect of anything said or any vote given by him in the Assembly or any`
  line `committee thereof, and no person shall be so liable in respect of the publicationby or under the authority`
  line `of such Assembly of any report,paper, votes or proceedings.`
  line
  line `(3) In other respects, the powers, privileges and immunities of the Legislative Assembly of ^2[the Union territory] and of the members and the committees thereof shall be such as are for the time being`
  line `enjoyed by the House of the People and its members and committees.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of sub-sections (1), (2) and (3) shall apply in relation to persons who by virtue of`
  line `this Act have the right to speak in, and otherwise to take part in the proceedings of, the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of ^2[the Union territory] or any committee thereof as they apply in relation to members of that`
  line Assembly.
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65 for "every Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987). .`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (15694)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 18
  title `Salaries and allowances of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15694&sectionno=17&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Members of the Legislative Assembly of ^1[the Union`
  line `territory] shall be entitled to receive such salaries and allowances as may from time to time be determined`
  line `by the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory by law and, until provision in that behalf is so made, such salaries and allowances as the Administrator may, with the approval of the President, by order`
  line determine.
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (15695)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 19
  title `Extent of legislative power.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15695&sectionno=18&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Legislative Assembly`
  line `of ^1[the Union territory] may make laws for the whole or any part of the Union territory with respect to`
  line `any of the matters enumerated in the State List or the Concurrent List in the Seventh Schedule to the`
  line `Constitution in so far as any such matter is applicable in relation to Union territories.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall derogate from the powers conferred on Parliament by the`
  line `Constitution to make laws with respect to any matter for ^1[the Union territory] or any part thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (15696)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 20
  title `Exemption of property of the Union from taxation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15696&sectionno=19&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The property of the Union shall, save in`
  line `so far as Parliament may by law otherwise provide, be exempted from all taxes imposed by or under any`
  line `law made by the Legislative Assembly of ^1[the Union territory] or by or under any other law in force in`
  line `^1[the Union territory]:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall, until Parliament by law otherwise provides, prevent any`
  line `authority within ^1[the Union territory] from levying any tax on any property of the Union to which such`
  line `property was immediately before the commencement of the Constitution liable or treated as liable, so long`
  line `as that tax continues to be levied in that Union territory.`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (15697)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 21
  title `Restrictions or laws passed by Legislative Assembly with respect to certain matters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15697&sectionno=20&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line ^1[1]
  line `The provisions of article 286, article 287 and article 288 shall apply in relation to any law passed by the Legislative Assembly of ^2[the Union territory] with respect to any of the matters referred to in those articles as they apply in relation to any law passed by the Legislature of a State with respect to those`
  line matters.
  line
  line `^3[(2) The provisions of article 304 shall, with the necessary modifications, apply in relation to any law`
  line `passed by the Legislative Assembly of ^2[the Union territory] with respect to any of the matters referred to`
  line `in that article as they apply in relation to any law passed by the Legislature of a State with respect to those`
  line matters.]
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Secton 20 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 83 of 1971, s. 5 (w.e.f. 16-2-1972).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 16-2-1972).`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (15698)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 22
  title `Inconsistency between laws made by Parliament and laws made by Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15698&sectionno=21&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `^1[21. Inconsistency between laws made by Parliament and laws made by Legislative`
  line `Assembly.--If any provision of a law made by the Legislative Assembly of`
  line `^2[the Union territory] with`
  line `respect to any matter enumerated in the State List in the Seventh Schedule to the Constitution is`
  line `repugnant to any provision of alaw made by Parliament with respect to that matter, whether passed before`
  line `or after the law made by the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory, or, if any provision of a law`
  line `made by the Legislative Assembly of ^2[the Union territory] with respect to any matter enumerated in the`
  line `Concurrent List in the Seventh Schedule to the Constitution is repugnant to any provision of any earlier`
  line `law, other than a law made by the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory, with respect to that matter,`
  line `then, in either case, the law made by Parliament, or, as the case may be, such earlier law shall prevail and`
  line `the law made by the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory shall, to the extent of the`
  line `repugnancy, be void:`
  line
  line `Provided that if such law made by the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory has been reserved`
  line `for the consideration of the President and has received his assent, such law shall prevail in that Union`
  line `territory:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing in this section shall prevent Parliament from enacting at any time any`
  line `law with respect to the same matter including a law adding to, amending, varying or repealing the law so`
  line `made by the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 29 of 1975, s. 4, for section 21 (w.e.f. 15-8-1975)`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (15699)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 23
  title `Sanction of the Administrator required for certain legislative proposals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15699&sectionno=22&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `No Bill or`
  line `amendment shall be introduced into, or moved in, the Legislative Assembly of ^1[the Union territory]`
  line `without the previous sanction of the Administrator, if such Bill or Amendment makes provision with`
  line `respect to any of the following matters, namely:―`
  line
  line `(a) constitution and organisation of the court of the Judicial Commissioner;`
  line
  line `(b) jurisdiction and powers of the court of the Judicial Commissioner with respect to any of the`
  line `matters in the State List or the Concurrent List in the Seventh Schedule to the Constitution.`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (15700)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 24
  title `Special provisions as to financial Bills.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15700&sectionno=23&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Bill or amendment shall not be introduced into,`
  line `or moved in, the Legislative Assembly of ^1[the Union territory] except on the recommendation of the`
  line `Administrator, if such Bill or Amendment makes provision for any of the following matters, namely:―`
  line
  line `(a) the imposition, abolition, remission, alteration or regulation of any tax;`
  line
  line `(b) the amendment of the law with respect to any financial obligations undertaken or to be`
  line `undertaken by the Government of the Union territory;`
  line
  line `(c) the appropriation of moneys out of the Consolidated Fund of the Union territory;`
  line
  line `(d) the declaring of any expenditure to be expenditure charged on the Consolidated Fund of the`
  line `Union territory or the increasing of the amount of any such expenditure;`
  line
  line `^2[(e) the receipt of money on account of the Consolidated Fund of the Union territory or the`
  line `public account of the Union territory or the custody or issue of such money or the audit of the account`
  line `of the Union territory]:`
  line
  line `Provided that no recommendation shall be required under this sub-section for the moving of an`
  line `amendment making provision for the reduction or abolition of any tax.`
  line
  line `(2) A Bill or Amendment shall not be deemed to make provision for any of the matters aforesaid by`
  line `reason only that it provides for the imposition of fines or other pecuniary penalties, or for the demand or`
  line `payment of fees for licences or fees for services rendered, or by reason that it provides for the imposition,`
  line `abolition, remission, alteration or regulation of any tax by any local authority or body for local purposes.`
  line
  line `(3) A Bill which, if enacted and brought into operation, would involve expenditure from the`
  line `Consolidated Fund of ^1[the Union territory] shall not be passed by the Legislative Assembly of the Union`
  line `territory unless the Administrator has recommended to that Assembly the consideration of the Bill.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 38 of 2001, s. 2, for clause (e) (w.e.f. 10-5-2006)`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (15701)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 25
  title `Procedure as to lapsing of Bills.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15701&sectionno=24&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Bill pending in the Legislative Assembly of ^1[the Union`
  line `territory] shall not lapse by reason of the prorogation of the Assembly.`
  line
  line `(2) A Bill which is pending in the Legislative Assembly of ^1[the Union territory] shall lapse on a`
  line `dissolution of the Assembly.`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (15702)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 26
  title `Assent to Bills.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15702&sectionno=25&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `^1[25. Assent to Bills.When a Bill has been passed by the Legislative Assembly of ^2[the Union`
  line `territory], it shall be presented to the Administrator and the Administrator shall declare either that he`
  line `assents to the Bill or that he withholds assent therefrom or that he reserves the Bill for the consideration`
  line `of the President:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Administrator may, as soon as possible after the presentation of the Bill to him for`
  line `assent, return the Bill if it is not a Money Bill together with a message requesting that the Assembly will`
  line `reconsider the Bill or any specified provisions thereof, and, in particular, will consider the desirability of`
  line `introducing any such amendments as he may recommend in his message and, when a Bill is so returned,`
  line `the Assembly will reconsider the Bill accordingly, and if the Bill is passed again with or without`
  line `amendment and presented to the Administrator for assent, the Administrator shall declare either that he`
  line `assents to the Bill or that he reserves the Bill for the consideration of the President:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Administrator shall not assent to, but shall reserve for the consideration of`
  line `the President, any Bill which,`
  line
  line `(a) in the opinion of the Administrator would, if it became law, so derogate from the powers of`
  line `the High Court as to endanger the position which that Court is, by the Constitution, designed to fill; or`
  line
  line `(b) relates to any of the matters specified in clause (1) of article 31A; or`
  line
  line `(c) the President may, by order, direct to be reserved for his consideration; or`
  line
  line `(d) relates to matters referred to in sub-section (5) or section 7 or section 17 or section 34 or`
  line `sub-section (6) of section 45 or in entry 1 or entry 2 of the State List in the Seventh Schedule to the`
  line `Constitution:`
  line
  line `Provided also that without prejudice to the provisions of the second proviso, the Administrator shall`
  line `not assent to, but shall reserve for the consideration of the President, any Bill which has been passed by`
  line `the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory of Mizoram and which relates to any area comprised in`
  line `any autonomous district in that Union territory under the Sixth Schedule to the Constitution.`
  line
  line `Explanation.For the purposes of this section and section 25A, a Bill shall be deemed to be a Money`
  line `Bill if it contains only provisions dealing with all or any of the matters specified in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 23 or any matter incidental to any of those matters and, in either case, there is endorsed thereon`
  line `the certificate of the Speaker of the Legislative Assembly signed by him that it is a Money Bill.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 83 of 1971, s. 7, for section 25 (w.e.f. 16-2-1972).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_25_a:
  sectionId (15703)
  sectionNo 25A
  orderNo 27
  title `Bills reserved for consideration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15703&sectionno=25A&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_25_a_content:
  string
  line `When a Bill is reserved by an Administrator for the`
  line `consideration of the President, the President shall declare either that he assents to the Bill or that he`
  line `withholds assent therefrom:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Bill is not a Money Bill, the President may direct the Administrator to return`
  line `the Bill to the Legislative Assembly together with such a message as is mentioned in the first proviso to`
  line `section 25 and, when a Bill is so returned, the Assembly shall reconsider it accordingly within a period of`
  line `six months from the date of receipt of such message and, if it is again passed by the Assembly with or`
  line `without amendment, it shall be presented again to the President for his consideration.]`
obj_root_law_sections_25_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (15704)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 28
  title `Requirements as to sanctions andrecommendations to be regarded as matters of procedure only.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15704&sectionno=26&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `No Act of the Legislative Assembly of ^1[the Union territory] and no provision in any such Act,`
  line `shall be invalid by reason only that some previous sanction or recommendation required by this Act was`
  line `not given, if assent to that Act was given ^2[by the Administrator, or, on being reserved by the`
  line `Administrator for the consideration of the President, by the President].`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 29 of 1975, s. 5, for "by the President" (w.e.f. 15- 8-1975).`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (15705)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 29
  title `Annual financial statement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15705&sectionno=27&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Administrator of each Union territory shall in respect of`
  line `every financial year cause to be laid before the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory, with the`
  line `previous approval of the President, a statement of the estimated receipts and expenditure of the Union`
  line `territory for that year, in this Part referred to as the "annual financial statement".`
  line
  line `(2) The estimates of expenditure embodied in the annual financial statement shall show separately—`
  line
  line `(a) the sums required to meet expenditure described by this Act as expenditure charged upon the`
  line `Consolidated Fund of the Union territory, and`
  line
  line `(b) the sums required to meet other expenditure proposed to be made from the Consolidated Fund`
  line `of the Union territory;`
  line
  line `and shall distinguish expenditure on revenue account from other expenditure.`
  line
  line `(3) The following expenditure shall be expenditure charged on the Consolidated Fund of each Union`
  line `territory:—`
  line
  line `(a) the emoluments and allowances of the Administrator and other expenditure relating to his`
  line `office as determined by the President by general or special order;`
  line
  line `(b) the charges payable in respect of loans advanced to the Union territory from the Consolidated`
  line `Fund of India including interest, sinking fund charges and redemption charges, and other expenditure`
  line `connected therewith;`
  line
  line `(c) the salaries and allowances of the Speaker and the Deputy Speaker of the Legislative`
  line Assembly;
  line
  line `(d) expenditure in respect of the salaries and allowances of a Judicial Commissioner;`
  line
  line `(e) any sums required to satisfy any judgment, decree or award of any court or arbitral tribunal;`
  line
  line `(f) expenditure incurred by the Administrator in the discharge of his special responsibility;`
  line
  line `(g) any other expenditure declared by the Constitution or by law made by Parliament or by the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of the Union territory to be so charged.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (15706)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 30
  title `Procedure in Legislative Assembly with respect to estimates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15706&sectionno=28&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) So much of the estimates as`
  line `relates to expenditure charged upon the Consolidated Fund of ^1[the Union territory] shall not be submitted`
  line `to the vote of the Legislative Assembly of ^1[the Union territory], but nothing in this sub-section shall be`
  line `construed as preventing the discussion in the Legislative Assembly of any of those estimates.`
  line
  line `(2) So much of the said estimates as relates to other expenditure shall be submitted in the form of`
  line `demands for grants to the Legislative Assembly, and the Legislative Assembly shall have power to assent,`
  line `or to refuse to assent, to any demand, or to assent to any demand subject to a reduction of the amount`
  line `specified therein.`
  line
  line `(3) No demand for a grant shall be made except on the recommendation of the Administrator.`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (15707)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 31
  title `Appropriation Bills.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15707&sectionno=29&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) As soon as may be after the grants under section 28 have been made`
  line `by the Assembly, there shall be introduced a Bill to provide for the appropriation out of the Consolidated`
  line `Fund of the Union territory of all moneys required to meet—`
  line
  line `(a) the grants so made by the Assembly, and`
  line
  line `(b) the expenditure charged on the Consolidated Fund of the Union territory but not exceeding in`
  line `any case the amount shown in the statement previously laid before the Assembly.`
  line
  line `(2) No amendment shall be proposed to any such Bill in the Legislative Assembly which will have the`
  line `effect of varying the amount or altering the destination of any grant so made or of varying the amount of`
  line `any expenditure charged on the Consolidated Fund of the Union territory and the decision of the person`
  line `presiding as to whether an amendment is inadmissible under this sub-section shall be final.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the other provisions of this Act, no money shall be withdrawn from the Consolidated`
  line `Fund of the Union territory except under appropriation made by law passed in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (15708)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 32
  title `Supplementary, additional or excess grants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15708&sectionno=30&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Administrator shall—`
  line
  line `(a) if the amount authorised by any law made in accordance with the provisions of section 29 to`
  line `be expended for a particular service for the current financial year is found to be insufficient for the`
  line `purposes of that year or when a need has arisen during the current financial year for supplementary or`
  line `additional expenditure upon some new service not contemplated in the annual financial statement for`
  line `that year, or`
  line
  line `(b) if any money has been spent on any service during a financial year in excess of the amount`
  line `granted for that service and for that year,`
  line
  line `cause to be laid before the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory, with the previous approval of the`
  line `President, another statement showing the estimated amount of that expenditure or cause to be presented to`
  line `the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory with such previous approval a demand for such excess, as`
  line `the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sections 27, 28 and 29 shall have effect in relation to any such statement and`
  line `expenditure or demand and also to any law to be made authorising the appropriation of moneys out of the Consolidated Fund of the Union territory to meet such expenditure or the grant in respect of such demand`
  line `as they have effect in relation to the annual financial statement and the expenditure mentioned therein or`
  line `to a demand for a grant and the law to be made for the authorisation of appropriation of moneys out of the`
  line `Consolidated Fund of the Union territory to meet such expenditure or grant.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (15709)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 33
  title `Votes on account.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15709&sectionno=31&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything in the foregoing provisions of this Part, the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of ^1[the Union territory] shall have power to make any grant in advance in respect`
  line `of the estimated expenditure for a part of any financial year pending the completion of the procedure`
  line `prescribed in section 28 for the voting of such grant and the passing of the law in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of section 29 in relation to that expenditure and the Legislative Assembly shall have power to`
  line `authorise by law the withdrawal of moneys from the Consolidated Fund of the Union territory for the`
  line `purposes for which the said grant is made.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sections 28 and 29 shall have effect in relation to the making of any grant under`
  line `sub-section (1) or to any law to be made under that sub-section as they have effect in relation to the`
  line `making of a grant with regard to any expenditure mentioned in the annual financial statement and the law`
  line `to be made for the authorisation of appropriation of moneys out of the Consolidated Fund of the Union`
  line `territory to meet such expenditure.`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (15710)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 34
  title `Authorisation of expenditure pending its sanction by Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15710&sectionno=32&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line Notwithstanding
  line `anything in the foregoing provisions of this Part, the Administrator may authorise such expenditure from`
  line `the Consolidated Fund of the Union territory as he deems necessary for a period of not more than six`
  line `months beginning with the date of the constitution of the Consolidated Fund of the Union territory,`
  line `pending the sanction of such expenditure by the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (15711)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 35
  title `Rules of procedure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15711&sectionno=33&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Legislative Assembly of ^1[the Union territory] may make rules for`
  line `regulating, subject to the provisions of this Act, its procedure and the conduct of its business:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Administrator shall, after consultation with the Speaker of the Legislative Assembly`
  line `and with the approval of the President, make rules--`
  line
  line `(a) for securing the timely completion of financial business;`
  line
  line `(b) for regulating the procedure of, and the conduct of business in, the Legislative Assembly in`
  line `relation to any financial matter or to any Bill for the appropriation of moneys out of the Consolidated`
  line `Fund of the Union territory;`
  line
  line `(c) for prohibiting the discussion of, or the asking of questions on, any matter which affects the`
  line `discharge of the functions of the Administrator in so far as he is required by this Act to act in his`
  line discretion.
  line
  line `(2) Until rules are made under sub-section (1), the rules of procedure and standing orders with respect`
  line `to the Legislative Assembly of the State of Uttar Pradesh in force immediately before the commencement`
  line `of this Act in ^2[the Union territory] shall have effect in relation to the Legislative Assembly of that Union`
  line `territory subject to such modifications and adaptations as may be made therein by the Administrator:`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 65, ibid., for "any Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987)`
  line
  line `3. The proviso omitted by Act 69 of 1986, s. 44 (w.e.f. 20-2-1987)`
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (15712)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 36
  title `Official language or languages of Union territory and language or languages to be used in Legislative Assemblythereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15712&sectionno=34&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Legislative Assembly of ^1[the Union territory] may by law`
  line `adopt any one or more of the languages in use in the Union territory or Hindi as the official language or`
  line `languages to be used for all or any of the official purposes of the Union territory:`
  line
  line `Provided that so long as the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory of Pondicherry does not`
  line `decide otherwise, the French language shall continue to be used as an official language of that Union`
  line `territory for the same official purposes for which it was being used in that territory immediately before the`
  line `commencement of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the President may by order direct—`
  line
  line `(i) that the official language of the Union shall be adopted for such of the official purposes of the`
  line `Union territory as may be specified in the order;`
  line
  line `(ii) that any other language shall also be adopted throughout the Union territory or such part`
  line `thereof for such of the official purposes of the Union territory as may be specified in the order, if the`
  line `President is satisfied that a substantial proportion of the population of the Union territory desires the`
  line `use of that other language for all or any of such purposes.`
  line
  line `(2) The business in the Legislative Assembly of ^1[the Union territory] shall be transacted in the`
  line `official language or languages of the Union territory or in Hindi or in English:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Speaker of the Legislative Assembly or person acting as such, as the case may be,`
  line `may permit any member who cannot adequately express himself in any of the languages aforesaid to`
  line `address the Assembly in his mother-tongue.`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (15713)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 37
  title `Language to be used for Acts, Bills, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15713&sectionno=35&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 34,`
  line `until Parliament by law otherwise provides, the authoritative texts—`
  line
  line `(a) of all Bills to be introduced or amendments thereto to be moved in the Legislative Assembly`
  line `of ^1[the Union territory],`
  line
  line `(b) of all Acts passed by the Legislative Assembly of ^1[the Union territory], and`
  line
  line `(c) of all orders, rules, regulations and bye-laws issued under any law made by the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of ^1[the Union territory],`
  line
  line `shall be in the English language:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Legislative Assembly of ^1[the Union territory] has prescribed any language`
  line `other than the English language for use in Bills introduced in, or Acts passed by, the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of the Union territory or in any order, rule, regulation or bye-law issued under any law made by`
  line `the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory, a translation of the same in the English language`
  line `published under the authority of the Administrator in the Official Gazette shall be deemed to be the`
  line `authoritative text thereof in the English language.`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (15714)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 38
  title `Restriction on discussion in the Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15714&sectionno=36&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `No discussion shall take place in the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of ^1[the Union territory] with respect to the conduct of any Judicial Commissioner`
  line `or of any judge of the Supreme Court or of a High Court in the discharge of his duties.`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (15715)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 39
  title `Courts not to inquire into proceedings of Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15715&sectionno=37&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) The validity of any`
  line `proceedings in the Legislative Assembly of ^1[the Union territory] shall not be called in question on the`
  line `ground of any alleged irregularity of procedure.`
  line
  line `(2) No officer or member of the Legislative Assembly of^1[the Union territory] in whom powers are`
  line `vested by or under this Act for regulating procedure or the conduct of business, or for maintaining order`
  line `in the Legislative Assembly shall be subject to the jurisdiction of any court in respect of the exercise by`
  line `him of those powers.`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (15716)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 40
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15716&sectionno=38&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `In this Part, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "associate member" means a member associated with the Delimitation Commission under`
  line `section 42 ^1[or with the Election Commission ^2[under section 43A or section 43C]];`
  line
  line `(b) "Delimitation Commission" means the Delimitation Commission constituted under section 3`
  line `of ^3[the Delimitation Act, 2002 (33 of 2002)];`
  line
  line `^4[(bb) "Election Commission" means the Election Commission appointed by the President under`
  line `article 324;]`
  line
  line `(c) "latest census figures" mean the census figures in ^5[the Union territory] ascertained at the`
  line `latest census of which the finally published figures are available;`
  line
  line `(d) "parliamentary constituency" means a constituency provided by law for the purpose of`
  line `elections to the House of the People from ^5[the Union territory] including the Union territory of Delhi.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 83 of 1971, s. 9 (w.e.f. 16-2-1972).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 29 of 1975, s. 7, for "under section 43A" (w.e.f. 15-8-1975).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 19 of 2005, s. 2, for "the Delimitation Commission Act, 1962 (61 of 1962)" (w.e.f. 21-5-2005).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 83 of 1971, s. 9 (w.e.f. 16-2-1972)`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (15717)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 41
  title `Assembly constituencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15717&sectionno=39&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of elections to the Legislative Assembly of ^1[the`
  line `Union territory], the Union territory shall be divided into single-member assembly constituencies in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Part in such manner that the population of each of the`
  line `constituencies shall, so far as practicable, be the same throughout the Union territory.`
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (15718)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 42
  title `Representation of Pondicherry in the House of the People.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15718&sectionno=40&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `There shall be allotted one seat to`
  line `the Union territory of Pondicherry in the House of the People and that Union territory shall form one`
  line `parliamentary constituency.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (15719)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 43
  title `Duties of Delimitation Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15719&sectionno=41&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of the Delimitation Commission—`
  line
  line `(a) to delimit the assembly constituencies in each Union territory, and`
  line
  line `(b) to determine, on the basis of the latest census figures, the number of seats to be reserved for`
  line `the scheduled castes and for the scheduled tribes in the Legislative Assembly of ^1[the Union territory] other than the Union territory of Goa, Daman and Diu, and the constituencies in which these seats`
  line `shall be so reserved.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall also be the duty of the Delimitation Commission—`
  line
  line `(a) to readjust, on the basis of the latest census figures, the division of each of the Union`
  line `territories of Delhi, Himachal Pradesh, Manipur and Tripura into parliamentary constituencies, ^2[the`
  line `number being 7, 4, 2 and 2];`
  line
  line `(b) to determine the constituency in which the seat shall be reserved for the scheduled castes or`
  line `for the scheduled tribes, as the case may be; and`
  line
  line `(c) to divide the Union territory of Goa, Daman and Diu into two single-member parliamentary`
  line constituencies.
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 19 of 1966, s. 37, for "the total number thereof remaining the same" (w.e.f. 13-6- 1966).`
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (15720)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 44
  title `Associate members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15720&sectionno=42&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of assisting the Delimitation Commission in its duties,`
  line `the Delimitation Commission shall associate with itself,―`
  line
  line `(a) in respect of the Union territory of Delhi, all the members of the House of the People`
  line `representing that Union territory;`
  line
  line `(b) in respect of each of the Union territories of Himachal Pradesh, Manipur and Tripura, all the`
  line `members of the House of the People representing that Union territory and three members of the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of that Union territory to be nominated by the Speaker of the Assembly from`
  line `among the members thereof;`
  line
  line `(c) in respect of the Union territory of Goa, Daman and Diu, the two members of the House of the`
  line `People representing that Union territory;`
  line
  line `(d) in respect of the Union territory of Pondicherry, three members of the Legislative Assembly`
  line `of that Union territory to be nominated by the Speaker of the Assembly from among the members`
  line thereof.
  line
  line `(2) The nomination of members of the several Legislative Assemblies under sub-section (1) shall be`
  line `made by the respective Speakers thereof as soon as practicable and shall be communicated to the`
  line `Delimitation Commission.`
  line
  line `(3) If owing to death or resignation the office of an associate member falls vacant, it shall be filled as`
  line `soon as practicable under and in accordance with the foregoing provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(4) None of the associate members shall have the right to vote or to sign any decision of the`
  line `Delimitation Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (15721)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 45
  title `Procedure as to delimitation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15721&sectionno=43&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of sections 7, 9, 10 and 11 of the Delimitation`
  line `Commission Act, 1962 (61 of 1962), shall apply, as far as may be, in relation to the delimitation of`
  line `parliamentary and assembly constituencies under this Part as they apply in relation to the delimitation of`
  line `parliamentary and assembly constituencies under that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43_a:
  sectionId (15722)
  sectionNo 43A
  orderNo 46
  title `Special provision for delimitation of constituencies of Mizoram Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 83 of 1971, s. 10 (w.e.f. 16-2-1972).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15722&sectionno=43A&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_43_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[43A. Special provision for delimitation of constituencies of Mizoram Legislative`
  line `Assembly.―(1) The provisions of sections 39 to 43 (both inclusive) shall not apply to the delimitation of`
  line `constituencies for the purpose of elections to the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory of Mizoram.`
  line
  line `(2) The Election Commission shall, in the manner herein provided, distribute the seats assigned to the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of the Union territory of Mizoram under sub-section (2) of section 3 to single`
  line `member assembly constituencies and delimit them on the basis of the latest census figures having regard`
  line `to the provisions of the Constitution and to the following provisions:―`
  line
  line `(a) all constituencies shall, as far as practicable, be geographically compact areas;`
  line
  line `(b) in delimiting the constituencies, regard shall be had to physical features, existing boundaries`
  line `of administrative units, facilities of communication and public convenience.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purpose of assisting in the performance of its functions under sub-section (2), the Election`
  line `Commission shall associate with itself as associate members—`
  line
  line `(a) all the persons who, having been elected to the Legislative Assembly of the State of Assam`
  line `from the Lungleh, Aijal East and Aijal West territorial constituencies, are members of that Assembly`
  line `immediately before the day appointed under clause (b) of section 2 of the North-Eastern Areas`
  line `(Reorganisation) Act, 1971 (81 of 1971); and`
  line
  line `(b) such three elected members of the District Council of the Mizo District as the Chairman`
  line `thereof may nominate:`
  line
  line `Provided that none of the associate members shall have a right to vote or sign any decision of the`
  line `Election Commission.`
  line
  line `(4) If, owing to death or resignation, the office of an associate member falls vacant, it shall be filled,`
  line `if practicable, in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(5) The Election Commission shall—`
  line
  line `(a) publish its proposals for the delimitation of constituencies, together with the dissenting`
  line `proposals, if any, of any associate member who desires publication thereof in the Official Gazette and`
  line `in such other manner as the Commission may consider fit, together with a notice inviting objections`
  line `and suggestions in relation to the proposals and specifying a date on or after which the proposals will`
  line `be further considered by it;`
  line
  line `(b) consider all objections and suggestions which may have been received by it before the date so`
  line specified;
  line
  line `(c) after consideration of objections and suggestions which may have been received by it before`
  line `the date so specified, determine by one or more orders the delimitation of constituencies and cause`
  line `such order or orders to be published in the Official Gazette; and upon such publication, the order or`
  line `orders shall have the full force of law and shall not be called in question in any court.`
  line
  line `(6) The Election Commission may, from time to time, by notification in the Official Gazette,―`
  line
  line `(a) correct any printing mistake in any order made under sub-section (5) or any error arising`
  line `therein from inadvertent slip or omission;`
  line
  line `(b) where the boundaries or name of any territorial division mentioned in any such order or orders`
  line `are or is altered, make such amendments as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for bringing such`
  line `order up-to- date.`
  line
  line `(7) Every order made under sub-section (5) and every notification issued under sub-section (6) shall`
  line `be laid as soon as may be after it is made or issued before the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory`
  line `of Mizoram.`
  line
  line `(8) All things done, and all steps taken, before the commencement of this Act in the Union territory of`
  line `Mizoram with a view to delimiting the territorial constituencies of that Union territory for purposes of`
  line `elections to the Legislative Assembly of that Union territory shall, in so far as they are in conformity with`
  line `the foregoing provisions of this section, be deemed to have been done or taken under those provisions as`
  line `if those provisions were in force at the time such things were done or such steps were taken.]`
obj_root_law_sections_43_b:
  sectionId (15723)
  sectionNo 43B
  orderNo 47
  title `Representation of Arunachal Pradesh in the House of the People.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 1975, s. 8 (w.e.f. 15-8-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15723&sectionno=43B&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_43_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[43B. Representation of Arunachal Pradesh in the House of the people.--In the House of the`
  line `People to be constituted after the general election to that House to be held after the commencement of the`
  line `Government of Union Territories (Amendment) Act, 1975 (29 of 1975) and thereafter, there shall be`
  line `allotted two seats to the Union territory of Arunachal Pradesh and the First Schedule to the Representation`
  line `of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950) shall be deemed to have been amended accordingly.]`
obj_root_law_sections_43_c:
  sectionId (15724)
  sectionNo 43C
  orderNo 48
  title `Special provisions for delimitation of parliamentary constituencies in Arunachal Pradesh and constituencies of Arunachal Pradesh Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 1975, s. 8 (w.e.f. 15-8-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15724&sectionno=43C&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_43_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[43C. Special provisions for delimitation of parliamentary constituencies in Arunachal Pradesh and constituencies of Arunachal Pradesh Legislative Assembly.--(1) The provisions of sections 39 to`
  line `43 (both inclusive) shall not apply to the delimitation of parliamentary constituencies in the Union`
  line `territory of Arunachal Pradesh or to the delimitation of constituencies for the purpose of elections to the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of that Union territory.`
  line
  line `(2) The Election Commission shall divide the Union territory of Arunachal Pradesh into two singlemember`
  line `parliamentary constituencies on the basis of the latest census figures.`
  line
  line `(3) The Election Commission shall also, in the manner herein provided, distribute the seats assigned`
  line `to the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory of Arunachal Pradesh under sub-section (2) of section`
  line `3 to single-member assembly constituencies and delimit them on the basis of the latest census figures`
  line `having regard to the following provisions:--`
  line
  line `(a) all constituencies shall, as far as practicable, be geographically compact areas;`
  line
  line `(b) every assembly constituency shall be so delimited as to fall only within one parliamentary`
  line constituency;
  line
  line `(c) in delimiting the constituencies, regard shall be had to physical features, existing boundaries`
  line `of administrative units facilities of communication and public convenience.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purpose of assisting in the performance of its functions under sub-sections (2) and (3), the`
  line `Election Commission shall associate with itself as associate members--`
  line
  line `(a) the member of the House of the People representing the Union territory of Arunachal Pradesh;`
  line
  line `(b) such five members of the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory of Arunachal Pradesh`
  line `as the Speaker of that Assembly shall, having regard to the composition of the Legislative Assembly,`
  line `nominate:`
  line
  line `Provided that none of the associate members shall have a right to vote or sign any decision of the`
  line `Election Commission.`
  line
  line `(5) If owing to death or resignation, the office of an associate member falls vacant, it shall be filled, if`
  line `practicable, in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `(6) The Election Commission shall--`
  line
  line `(a) publish its proposals for the delimitation of constituencies together with the dissenting`
  line `proposals, if any, of any associate member who desires publication thereof in the Official Gazette and`
  line `in such other manner as the Commission may consider fit, together with a notice inviting objections`
  line `and suggestions in relation to the proposals and specifying a date on or after which the proposals will`
  line `be further considered by it;`
  line
  line `(b) consider all objections and suggestions which may have been received by it before the date so`
  line specified;
  line
  line `(c) after consideration of objections and suggestions which may have been received by it before`
  line `the date so specified, determine by one or more orders the delimitation of constituencies and cause`
  line `such order or orders to be published in the Official Gazette; and upon such publication, the order or`
  line `orders shall have the full force of law and shall not be called in question in any court.`
  line
  line `(7) The Election Commission may, from time to time, by notification in the Official Gazette,--`
  line
  line `(a) correct any printing mistake in any order made under sub-section (6) or any error arising`
  line `therein from inadvertent slip or omission;`
  line
  line `(b) where the boundaries or name of any territorial division mentioned in any such order or orders`
  line `are or is altered, make such amendments as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for bringing such`
  line `order up-to-date.`
  line
  line `(8) Every order made under sub-section (6) and every notification issued under sub-section (7) shall`
  line `be laid as soon as may be after it is made or issued before the House of the People and the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of the Union territory of Arunachal Pradesh.`
  line
  line `(9) All things done, and all steps taken, before the commencement of this Act in the Union territory of`
  line `Arunachal Pradesh with a view to delimiting the territorial constituencies of that Union territory for`
  line `purposes of elections to the Legislative Assembly of that Union territory shall, in so far as they are in`
  line `conformity with the foregoing provisions of this section, be deemed to have been done or taken under`
  line `those provisions as if these provisions were in force at the time such things were done or such steps were`
  line taken.]
obj_root_law_sections_43_d:
  sectionId (15725)
  sectionNo 43D
  orderNo 49
  title `Special provision for determination of constituencies in the Legislative Assembly of Goa, Daman and Diu for Scheduled Castes and Scheduled Tribes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 86 of 1976, s. 3 (w.e.f. 30-9-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15725&sectionno=43D&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_43_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[43D. Special provision for determination of constituencies in the Legislative Assembly of Goa,`
  line `Daman and Diu for Scheduled Castes and Scheduled Tribes.―(1) The Election Commission shall`
  line `determine on the basis of the latest census figures—`
  line
  line `(i) the number of seats to be reserved for the Scheduled Castes and for the Scheduled Tribes in`
  line `the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory of Goa, Daman and Diu (hereafter in this section`
  line `referred to as the Legislative Assembly) having regard to the provisions of sub-section (5) of section`
  line `3; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the constituencies in which those seats shall be so reserved having regard to the provisions of`
  line `clause (c), or, as the case may be, clause (d), of sub-section (1) of section 9 of the Delimitation Act`
  line `and without altering the extent of any constituency as delimited by the Delimitation Commission.`
  line
  line `(2) The Election Commission shall—`
  line
  line `(a) publish its proposals for the determination of the constituencies in which seats shall be`
  line `reserved for the Scheduled Castes or for the Scheduled Tribes, as the case may be, in the Gazette of`
  line `India and in the Official Gazette of the Union territory of Goa, Daman and Diu and also in such other`
  line `manner as the Election Commission may consider fit, together with a notice inviting objections and`
  line `suggestions in relation to the proposals and specifying a date on or after which the proposals will be`
  line `further considered by it;`
  line
  line `(b) consider all objections and suggestions which may have been received by it before the date so`
  line specified;
  line
  line `(c) after consideration of objections and suggestions which may have been received by it before`
  line `the date so specified, determine by one or more orders the number of seats to be reserved for the`
  line `Scheduled Castes or for the Scheduled Tribes, as the case may be, in the Legislative Assembly and`
  line `the constituencies in which those seats shall be so reserved and cause such order or orders to be`
  line `published in the Gazette of India and in the Official Gazette of the Union territory of Goa, Daman and`
  line `Diu; and upon such publication in the Gazette of India, the order or orders shall have the full force of`
  line `law and shall not be called in question in any court and the Second Schedule to the Representation of`
  line `the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950) and the order made by the Delimitation Commission under section`
  line `9 of the Delimitation Act in relation to the Legislative Assembly shall be deemed to have been`
  line `amended accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (4), the re-adjustment of representation of any territorial`
  line `constituencies in the Legislative Assembly necessitated by any order made by the Election Commission`
  line `under this section, shall apply in relation to every election to the Legislative Assembly held after the`
  line `publication in the Gazette of India, under sub-section (2), of such order.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing contained in the foregoing sub-sections shall affect the representation in the Legislative`
  line `Assembly existing on the date of publication in the Gazette of India, under sub-section (2), of any order`
  line `made by the Election Commission.`
  line
  line `(5) The Election Commission may, from time to time, by notification in the Gazette of India and in`
  line `the Official Gazette of the Union territory of Goa, Daman and Diu—`
  line
  line `(a) correct any printing mistake in any order made under sub-section (2) or any error arising`
  line `therein from inadvertent slip or omission;`
  line
  line `(b) where the boundaries or name of any territorial division mentioned in any such order are, or`
  line `is, altered, make such amendments as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for bringing such order`
  line up-to-date.
  line
  line `(6) Every order made under sub-section (2) and every notification issued under sub-section (5) shall`
  line `be laid, as soon as may be, after it is made or issued before the Legislative Assembly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section,—`
  line
  line `(a) "Delimitation Act" means the Delimitation Act, 1972 (76 of 1972);`
  line
  line `(b) "Delimitation Commission" means the Delimitation Commission constituted under section 3`
  line `of the Delimitation Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_43_e:
  sectionId (15726)
  sectionNo 43E
  orderNo 50
  title `Special provisions as to readjustment of territorial constituencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_e_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_e_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15726&sectionno=43E&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_43_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[43E. Special provisions as to readjustment of territorial constituencies.―Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in sections 38 to 43D (both inclusive), until the relevant figures for the first census`
  line `taken after the year ^2[2026] have been published, it shall not be necessary to readjust the division of each`
  line `Union territory into territorial constituencies and any reference to the "latest census figures" in this Part`
  line `shall be construed as a reference to the ^3[2001] census figures.]`
obj_root_law_sections_43_e_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 19 of 1984, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-3-1984).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 19 of 2005, s. 4, for "2000" (w.e.f. 21-5-2005).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "1971" (w.e.f. 21-5-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_43_f:
  sectionId (15727)
  sectionNo 43F
  orderNo 51
  title `Special provision as to readjustment of territorial constituencies on the basis of 2001 census.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_f_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 5 of 2006, s. 2 (w.e.f. 31-3-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15727&sectionno=43F&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_43_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[43F. Special provision as to readjustment of territorial constituencies on the basis of 2001`
  line `census.―Notwithstanding the publication of orders under sub-section (1) of section 10 of the`
  line `Delimitation Act, 2002 (33 of 2002) or anything contained in sub-section (2) or sub-section (4) of the said`
  line `section, any readjustment in the division of Union territory into territorial constituencies by the`
  line `Delimitation Commission under the said Act, on the basis of 2001 census shall take effect from such date`
  line `as the Central Government may, by order, published in the Official Gazette, specify and until such`
  line `readjustment takes effect, any election to the Legislative Assembly may be held on the basis of the`
  line `territorial constituencies existing before such readjustment.]`
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (15728)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 52
  title `Council of Ministers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15728&sectionno=44&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a Council of Ministers in each Union territory with the`
  line `Chief Minister at the head to aid and advise the Administrator in the exercise of his functions in relation`
  line `to matters with respect to which the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory has power to make laws`
  line `except in so far as he is required by or under this Act to act in his discretion or by or under any law to`
  line `exercise any judicial or quasi-judicial functions:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in case of difference of opinion between the Administrator and his Ministers on any`
  line `matter, the Administrator shall refer it to the President for decision and act according to the decision given`
  line `thereon by the President, and pending such decision it shall be competent for the Administrator in any`
  line `case where the matter is in his opinion so urgent that it is necessary for him to take immediate action, to`
  line `take such action or to give such direction in the matter as he deems necessary:`
  line
  line `^1* ****`
  line
  line ^2*****
  line
  line `(3) If and in so far as any special responsibility of the Administrator is involved under this Act, he`
  line `shall, in the exercise of his functions, act in his discretion.`
  line
  line `(4) If any question arises as to whether any matter is or is not a matter as respects which the`
  line `Administrator is by or under this Act required to act in his discretion, the decision of the Administrator`
  line `thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `(5) If any question arises as to whether any matter is or is not a matter as respects which the`
  line `Administrator is required by any law to exercise any judicial or quasi-judicial functions, the decision of`
  line `the Administrator thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `(6) The question whether any, and if so what, advice was tendered by Ministers to the Administrator`
  line `shall not be inquired into in any court.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.The second proviso omitted by Act 34 of 1986, s. 41 (w.e.f. 20-2-1987).`
  line
  line `2. Sub-section (2) omitted by Act 69 of 1986, s. 44 (w.e.f. 20-2-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (15729)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 53
  title `Other provisions as to Ministers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15729&sectionno=45&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Minister shall be appointed by the President`
  line `and the other Ministers shall be appointed by the President on the advice of the Chief Minister.`
  line
  line `(2) The Ministers shall hold office during the pleasure of the President.`
  line
  line `(3) The Council of Ministers shall be collectively responsible to the Legislative Assembly of the`
  line `Union territory.`
  line
  line `(4) Before a Minister enters upon his office, the Administrator shall administer to him the oaths of`
  line `office and of secrecy according to the forms set out for the purpose in the First Schedule.`
  line
  line `(5) A Minister who for any period of six consecutive months is not a member of the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of the Union territory shall at the expiration of that period cease to be a Minister.`
  line
  line `(6) The salaries and allowances of Ministers shall be such as the Legislative Assembly of the Union`
  line `territory may from time to time by law determine, and until the Legislative Assembly so determines, shall`
  line `be determined by the Administrator with the approval of the President.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (15730)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 54
  title `Conduct of business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15730&sectionno=46&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) The President shall make rules—`
  line
  line `(a) for the allocation of business to the Ministers; and`
  line
  line `(b) for the more convenient transaction of business with the Ministers including the procedure to`
  line `be adopted in the case of a difference of opinion between the Administrator and the Council of`
  line `Ministers or a Minister.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, all executive action of the Administrator, whether taken on`
  line `the advice of his Ministers or otherwise, shall be expressed to be taken in the name of the Administrator.`
  line
  line `(3) Orders and other instruments made and executed in the name of the Administrator, shall be`
  line `authenticated in such manner as may be specified in rules to be made by the Administrator, and the`
  line `validity of an order or instrument which is so authenticated shall not be called in question on the ground`
  line `that it is not an order or instrument made or executed by the Administrator.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (15731)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 55
  title `Consolidated Fund of the Union territory.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15731&sectionno=47&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) As from such date as the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint in this behalf, all revenues received in ^1`
  line `[the Union`
  line `territory] by the Government of India or the Administrator of the Union territory in relation to any matter`
  line `with respect to which the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory has power to make laws, and all`
  line `grants made and ^2[all loans advanced to the Union territory from the Consolidated Fund of India and all`
  line `loans raised by the Government of India or the Administrator of the Union territory upon the security of`
  line `the Consolidated Fund of the Union territory] and all moneys received by the Union territory in`
  line `repayment of loans shall form one Consolidated Fund to be entitled "the Consolidated Fund of the Union`
  line `territory".`
  line
  line `(2) No moneys out of the Consolidated Fund of ^1[the Union territory] shall be appropriated except in`
  line `accordance with, and for the purposes and in the manner provided in, this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The custody of the Consolidated Fund of ^1[the Union territory], the payment of moneys into such`
  line `Fund, the withdrawal of moneys therefrom and all other matters connected with or ancillary to those`
  line `matters shall be regulated by rules made by the Administrator with the approval of the President.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 38 of 2001, s. 3, for "all loans advanced to the Union territory from the Consolidated Fund of India"`
  line `(w.e.f. 10-5-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_47_a:
  sectionId (15732)
  sectionNo 47A
  orderNo 56
  title `Public Account of the Union territory and moneys credited to it.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-5-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15732&sectionno=47A&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_47_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[47A. Public Account of the Union territory and moneys credited to it.―(1) As from such date`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint in this behalf, all other`
  line `public moneys received by or on behalf of the Administrator shall be credited to a Public Account entitled`
  line `"the Public Account of the Union territory".`
  line
  line `(2) The custody of public moneys, other than those credited to the Consolidated Fund of the Union`
  line `territory or the Contingency Fund of the Union territory, received by or on behalf of the Administrator,`
  line `their payment into the Public Account of the Union territory and the withdrawal of moneys from such`
  line `account and all other matters connected with or ancillary to the aforesaid matters shall be regulated by`
  line `rules made by the Administrator with the approval of the President.]`
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (15733)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 57
  title `Contingency Fund of the Union territory.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15733&sectionno=48&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be established a Contingency Fund`
  line `in the nature of an imprest to be entitled "the Contingency Fund of the Union territory, into which shall be`
  line `paid from and out of the Consolidated Fund of the Union territory such sums as may, from time to time, be determined by law made by the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory; and the said Fund shall be`
  line `held by the Administrator to enable advances to be made by him out of such Fund.`
  line
  line `(2) No advances shall be made out of the Contingency Fund of the Union territory except for the`
  line `purposes of meeting unforeseen expenditure pending authorisation of such expenditure by the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of the Union territory under appropriations made by law.`
  line
  line `(3) The Administrator may make rules regulating all matters connected with or ancillary to the`
  line `custody of, the payment of moneys into, and the withdrawal of moneys from, the Contingency Fund of`
  line `the Union territory.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48_a:
  sectionId (15734)
  sectionNo 48A
  orderNo 58
  title `Borrowing upon the security of the Consolidated Fund of the Union territory.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 38 of 2001, s. 5 (w.e.f. 10-5-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15734&sectionno=48A&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_48_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[48A. Borrowing upon the security of the Consolidated Fund of the Union Territory.--(1) The`
  line `executive power of the Union extends to borrowing upon the security of the Consolidated Fund of the`
  line `Union territory within such limits, if any, as may, from time to time, be fixed by Parliament by law and to`
  line `the giving of guarantees within such limits, if any, as may be so fixed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the powers exercisable by the Government of India under this sub-section shall also be`
  line `exercisable by the Administrator subject to such conditions, if any, as the Government of India may think`
  line `fit to impose.`
  line
  line `(2) Any sums required for the purpose of invoking a guarantee shall be charged on the Consolidated`
  line `Fund of the Union territory.]`
obj_root_law_sections_48_b:
  sectionId (15735)
  sectionNo 48B
  orderNo 59
  title `Form of accounts of the Union territory.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_b_content
  footnotes `1. 1. Ins. by Act 38 of 2001, s. 5 (w.e.f. 10-5-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15735&sectionno=48B&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_48_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[48B. Form of accounts of the Union territory.--The accounts of the Union territory shall be kept in`
  line `such form as the Administrator may, after obtaining advice of the Comptroller and Auditor-General of`
  line `India and with the approval of the President, prescribe by rules.]`
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (15736)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 60
  title `Audit reports.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15736&sectionno=49&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `The reports of the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India relating to the`
  line `accounts of ^1[the Union territory] for any period subsequent to the date referred to in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 47 shall be submitted to the Administrator who shall cause them to be laid before the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of the Union territory.`
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (15737)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 61
  title `Relation of Administrator and his Ministers to President.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15737&sectionno=50&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything in this`
  line `Act, the Administrator and his Council of Ministers shall be under the general control of, and comply`
  line `with such particular directions, if any, as may from time to time be given by, the President.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (15738)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 62
  title `Provision in case of failure of constitutional machinery.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15738&sectionno=51&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `If the President, on receipt of a`
  line `report from the Administrator of ^1[the Union territory] or otherwise, is satisfied,―`
  line
  line `(a) that a situation has arisen in which the administration of the Union territory cannot be carried`
  line `on in accordance with the provisions of this Act, or`
  line
  line `(b) that for the proper administration of the Union territory it is necessary or expedient so to do,`
  line
  line `the President may, by order, suspend the operation of all or any of the provisions of this Act for such`
  line `period as he thinks fit and make such incidental and consequential provisions as may appear to him to be`
  line `necessary or expedient for administering the Union territory in accordance with the provisions of article`
  line 239.
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (15739)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 63
  title `Authorisation of expenditure by President.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15739&sectionno=52&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `^1[52. Authorisation of expenditure by President.―Where the Legislative Assembly of ^2[the Union`
  line `territory] is dissolved, or its functioning as such Assembly remains suspended, on account of an order`
  line `under section 51, it shall be competent for the President to authorise when the House of the People is not`
  line `in session expenditure from the Consolidated Fund of that Union territory pending the sanction of such`
  line `expenditure by Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 1980, s. 2 (w.e.f. 25-9-1979).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (15740)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 64
  title `Provisions for election to Parliament from Goa, Daman and Diu, and Pondicherry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15740&sectionno=53&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) As`
  line `soon as practicable after the commencement of this Act, elections shall be held in accordance with law―`
  line
  line `(a) to fill the seats in the House of the People allotted to the Union territory of Goa, Daman and`
  line `Diu; and`
  line
  line `(b) to fill the seat in the House of the People and the seat in the Council of States allotted to the`
  line `Union territory of Pondicherry.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, the members`
  line `nominated to represent the Union territory of Goa, Daman and Diu in the House of the People shall`
  line `continue to be such until the election of the members to fill the two seats in that House allotted to that`
  line `Union territory:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the dates of election of the members are different, the members so nominated`
  line `shall cease to be members of that House on the earlier of those two dates.`
  line
  line `Explanation.―In this sub-section, the expression "date of election" has the same meaning as in`
  line `section 67A of the Representation of the People Act, 1951 (43 of 1951).`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (15741)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 65
  title `Transitional provisions for administration of justice in certain areas in the Union territory of Mizoram.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 83 of 1971, s. 12, for section 54 (w.e.f. 16-2-1972)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15741&sectionno=54&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `^1[54. Transitional provisions for administration of justice in certain areas in the Union territory`
  line `of Mizoram.―On and from the commencement of this Act in the Union territory of Mizoram and until`
  line `other provisions in this behalf are made by a competent Legislature or other competent authority, the`
  line `administration of justice in those areas of that Union territory which are not comprised in any autonomous`
  line `district under the Sixth Schedule to the Constitution shall be carried on, so far as may be, in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of paragraphs 4 and 5 of that Schedule, as if those areas were comprised in an`
  line `autonomous district under that Schedule and the provisions of the said paragraphs were in force in those`
  line `areas and for this purpose,―`
  line
  line `(i) all powers and functions of a District Council under the provisions of the said paragraph 4`
  line `shall be exercised and discharged by the Administrator or any officer appointed by him in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(ii) the said paragraph 5 shall have effect as if references to the District Council, the Regional`
  line `Council and the courts constituted by the District Council, by whatever form of words, had been`
  line `omitted therefrom; and`
  line
  line `(iii) references to Governor in the said paragraphs 4 and 5 shall be construed as references to the`
  line Administrator.]
obj_root_law_sections_54_a:
  sectionId (15742)
  sectionNo 54A
  orderNo 66
  title `Provision as to provisional Legislative Assembly of Arunachal Pradesh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 1975, s. 10 (w.e.f. 15-8-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15742&sectionno=54A&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_54_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[54A. Provision as to provisional Legislative Assembly of Arunachal Pradesh.―(1)`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act (including provisions relating to the strength of the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of the Union territory of Arunachal Pradesh), until the Legislative Assembly of the`
  line `Union territory of Arunachal Pradesh has been duly constituted and summoned to meet for the first`
  line `session under and in accordance with the provisions of this Act, there shall be a provisional Legislative`
  line `Assembly which shall consist of members, being those persons referred to in clauses (b), (c) and (d) of`
  line `section 3 of the North-East Frontier Agency (Administration) Supplementary Regulation, 1971`
  line `(4 of 1971) and who are functioning, immediately before the commencement of this Act in the Union`
  line `territory of Arunachal Pradesh, as members of the Pradesh Council constituted under the said section 3.`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of the members of the provisional Legislative Assembly shall expire`
  line `immediately before the first meeting of the Legislative Assembly duly constituted after the first general`
  line `election to that Assembly.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisional Legislative Assembly constituted under this section shall, for so long as it is in`
  line `existence, be deemed to be the Legislative Assembly duly constituted under this Act and accordingly the`
  line `other provisions of this Act, so far as may be, apply in relation to the provisional Legislative Assembly as`
  line `they apply in relation to the Legislative Assembly.]`
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (15743)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 67
  title `Contracts and suits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15743&sectionno=55&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `For the removal of doubts it is hereby declared that—`
  line
  line `(a) all contracts in connection with the administration of ^1[the Union territory] are contracts made`
  line `in the exercise of the executive power of the Union;`
  line
  line `(b) all suits and proceedings in connection with the administration of ^1[the Union territory] shall`
  line `be instituted by or against the Government of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (15744)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 68
  title `Power of President to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 65, ibid., for "any Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15744&sectionno=56&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in relation to the transition`
  line `from the provisions of any of the laws repealed by this Act or in giving effect to the provisions of this Act`
  line `and, in particular, in relation to the constitution of the Legislative Assembly for ^1[the Union territory], the`
  line `President may by order do anything not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act which appear to him`
  line `to be necessary or expedient for the purpose of removing the difficulty.`
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (15745)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 69
  title `Amendment to certain enactments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15745&sectionno=57&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) The enactments specified in the Second Schedule―`
  line
  line `(a) shall, together with all rules, notifications and orders made or issued thereunder, extend to and`
  line `come into force in the Union territories of Goa, Daman and Diu, and Pondicherry; and`
  line
  line `(b) shall be subject to the amendments mentioned in the fourth column of the said Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) All things done, and all steps taken, before the commencement of this Act in connection with the`
  line `preparation or revision of electoral rolls for the purpose of elections to the House of the People from the`
  line `Union territories of Goa, Daman and Diu, and Pondicherry, and to the Legislative Assemblies of those`
  line `Union territories shall, in so far as they are in conformity with the provisions of the Representation of the`
  line `People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950), as amended by this Act, be deemed to have been done in accordance with`
  line law.
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (15746)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 70
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 65, for "a Union territory" (w.e.f. 30-5-1987).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637&sectionId=15746&sectionno=58&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00002_196320_1517807317637
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) The following laws are hereby repealed:―`
  line
  line `(a) the Territorial Councils Act, 1956 (103 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(b) the Decree No. 46-2381, dated the 25th October, 1946, as subsequently amended, relating to`
  line `the Representative Assembly of the State of Pondicherry;`
  line
  line `(c) the Decree No. 47-1490, dated the 12th August, 1947, as subsequently amended, relating to`
  line `the setting up of a Council of Government in the State of Pondicherry;`
  line
  line `(d) the State of Pondicherry (Representation of the People) Order, 1955, in so far as it relates to`
  line `the Representative Assembly of Pondicherry.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the repeal of the Territorial Councils Act, 1956 (103 of 1956),―`
  line
  line `(a) every officer and other employee of the Territorial Council of ^1[the Union territory] serving`
  line `under the Council immediately before such repeal shall become an officer or other employee of`
  line `Government and shall be employed in connection with the administration of the Union territory with`
  line `such designation as the Administrator may determine and shall hold office by the same tenure and at`
  line `the same remuneration and on the same terms and conditions of service as he would have but for such`
  line `repeal held the same and shall continue to do so unless and until such tenure, remuneration and terms`
  line `and conditions are duly altered by the Administrator:`
  line
  line `Provided that―`
  line
  line `(i) the tenure, remuneration and terms and conditions of service of any such officer or other`
  line `employee shall not be altered to his disadvantage without the previous sanction of the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(ii) any service rendered by any such officer or other employee before such repeal shall be`
  line `deemed to be service rendered in connection with the administration of the Union territory;`
  line
  line `(iii) the Administrator may employ any such officer or other employee in the discharge of such`
  line `functions as the Administrator may think proper and every such officer or other employee shall`
  line `discharge those functions accordingly;`
  line
  line `(b) anything done or any action taken (including any notification, order, scheme, rule, form,`
  line `notice or bye-law made or issued, any licence or permission granted) under the repealed Act shall in`
  line `so far as it is not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, continue in force unless and until it is`
  line `superseded by anything done or any action taken in accordance with law;`
  line
  line `(c) all debts, obligations and liabilities incurred, all contracts entered into and all matters and`
  line `things engaged to be done by, with or for the Territorial Council before such repeal shall be deemed`
  line `to have been incurred, entered into or engaged to be done in exercise of the executive power of the`
  line `Union for the purposes of the administration of the Union territory;`
  line
  line `(d) all assessments, valuations, measurements or divisions made by the Territorial Council shall,`
  line `in so far as they are not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, continue in force unless and until hey are superseded by any assessment, valuation, measurement or division made by the`
  line `Administrator in accordance with law;`
  line
  line `(e) all properties, movable and immovable, and all interests of whatsoever nature and kind, vested`
  line `in the Territorial Council immediately before such repeal shall, with all rights of whatsoever`
  line `description, used, enjoyed or possessed by that Council, vest in the Union for the purposes of the`
  line `administration of the Union territory;`
  line
  line `(f) all rates, taxes, cesses, fees, rents, fares and other charges which immediately before such`
  line `repeal were being lawfully levied by the Territorial Council shall continue to be levied at the same`
  line `rate at which they were being levied by the Council immediately before such repeal until provision to`
  line `the contrary is made by law;`
  line
  line `(g) all rates, taxes, cesses, fees, rents, fares and other charges due to the Territorial Council`
  line `immediately before such repeal shall be deemed to be due to the Union in connection with the`
  line `administration of the Union territory;`
  line
  line `(h) all suits, prosecutions and other legal proceedings instituted or which might have been`
  line `instituted by or against the Territorial Council may be continued or instituted by or against the`
  line `Government of India.`
